Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, said here Wednesday that the government had closely monitored the avian flu situation.
Macao is fully prepared for any possible outbreak of the bird flu although no case of H5N1 virus has been found so far, a doctor with the Government Hospital said.
Experts with China's National Influenza Center confirmed that no cases of H5N1 virus infection have been discovered in the inland areas, even though the strain has been detected a small group of Hong Kong residents.
